<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5027874>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 2. anatomy and histology of Anthopleura mariscali, new species. A. Longitudinal section through a marginal projection. Each projection bears an acrorhagus (A) on the oral surface and several verrucae (V) on the adoral surface. F, fosse. Scale = 0.5 mm. B. Longitudinal section through tip of a tentacle, showing apical pore (arrow). Scale = 30 m. C. Cross section of marginal sphincter muscle. Scale = 50 m. D. Longitudinal section through a verruca. Scale = 60 m. E. Cross section through mesentery proximal to actinopharynx, showing retractor muscle (R) and parietal muscle (P). Arrow indicates pennon of parietobasilar muscle. Scale = 90 m." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/5027874/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.416.1.1>
